title: Nicol kicks off title defence of US Open with easy victory
text:
Nicol kicks off title defence of US Open with easy victory Published: 12 October 2015 8:02 PM 
Datuk Nicol David kicks off her title defence in the 2015 US Squash Championships with a straight sets victory. – Reuters filepic, October 12, 2015. Malaysian squash queen and world number two Datuk Nicol David kicked off her title defence in the 2015 US Squash Championships with a straight sets victory in Philadelphia, United States. 
In the opening match early Monday, Nicol, the second seed defeated Hong Kong qualifier, Joey Chan 11-6, 11-9, 11-8 to sail into the second round. 
Nicol who is gunning for her third title of the season, will play against 12th seed Nouran Gohar of Egypt late Monday. 
Nouran, who is also the world junior champion, moved into the second round by defeating her compatriot Kazy Emad El Defrawy 11-5, 11-6, 11-7 in another opening round match. 
For the record, Nicol has won two titles so far this season – Cleveland Classic in Ohio, United States in February and the 2015 Women's Asian Individual Championship in Kuwait in May. 
Malaysia's number two Delia Arnold, who defeated unheralded Nicolette Fernandes of Guyana in her opening match on Sunday, will face a mammoth task in the second round when facing world number four, Camille Serme of France. 
Malaysia's representation in the men's category ended yesterday after Mohd Nafiizwan Adnan lost 9-11, 3-11, 7-11 to fifth seed and former three-time world champion Ramy Ashour from Egypt in the opening round. – Bernama, October 12,
